detailedDescription.articleBody: Regina Belle is an American singer–songwriter and actress who first started her career in the mid–1980s. Known for her singles, "Baby Come to Me" and "Make It Like It Was", Belle's most notable for two hit duets, both with Peabo Bryson: "Without You", the love theme from the comedy film Leonard Part 6, recorded in 1987 and "A Whole New World", the main theme of the Disney's animated feature film Aladdin, recorded in 1992, with which Belle and Bryson won the Grammy award.
